    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-23T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-23T21:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/5–2340: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Keith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-23T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 23, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 24—12:53 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Department’s telegram No. 84, May 23, noon.<note n="79" xml:id="d73fn1">See
                        footnote 29, <ref target="#pg_16">p. 16</ref>.</note> I have just returned
                    from interview with Foreign Minister<note n="80" xml:id="d73fn2">Luis López de
                        Mesa.</note> at his home. He <pb facs="0070" n="58" xml:id="pg_58"/>
                    personally fully approves rapid carrying out of proposed plan but cannot give me
                    official answer until after seeing President<note n="81" xml:id="d73fn3">Eduardo
                        Santos.</note> tomorrow morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Keith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
